                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Clayton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraph rase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay instructs Mr. Clayton to inquire into the circumstances connected with
                    the imprisonment of Harding and Dugat, which took place at Matamoros, for a
                    technical but insignificant infraction of local laws, and if the facts in the
                    case seem to warrant it to use his good offices to effect their release.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
